Always scan only networks you own or have explicit written permission to test.

Unauthorized port scanning can violate laws like the Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (CFAA) or GDPR.

Safe use cases:

✅ Your own servers/networks

✅ Authorized penetration tests

✅ Controlled lab/educational environments

Avoid:

❌ Scanning government, financial, or critical infrastructure systems

❌ Using scanners for malicious reconnaissance
